We also define some utility functions for data processing

# convert categories to int 1..n in the order given
encode.categorical <- function(column, categories) {
  factor(column, level = categories)
}

# convert bool to int true = 1, false = 2
encode.bool <- function(column) {
  encode.categorical(column, c("true", "false"))
}

# convert categories to int 1..n in the order given
encode.orderedcategorical <- function(column, categories) {
  as.ordered(encode.categorical(column, categories))
}

# Change likert scales from -3 to 3 to 1 to 7
encode.likert <- function(column) {
  as.ordered(column + 4)
}

We use the utility function to set the correct types for each data column

Pick out some subdata sets

d.sessions <- d %>% group_by(session) %>% summarise(
  across(task_completion, min),
  across(c(
    education_level, 
    education_field, 
    work_domain, 
    work_experience_java, 
    work_experience_programming, 
    workplace_coding_standards, 
    workplace_pair_programming, 
    workplace_peer_review, 
    workplace_td_tracking
  ), first)
  ) 

d.sessions.completed <- d.sessions %>% filter(task_completion == "Completed")
d.only_submitted <- d %>% filter(task_completion != "Not submitted")

Model:

sonarqube_issues0 <- brm(
  sonarqube_issues ~ 1 
  + high_debt_version
  #    + mo(education_level_oc7)
  #    + education_field_c2
  #    + work_exp_field_c6
  #    + prof_prog_exp_months
  #    + prof_java_exp_months
  #    + wp_peer_review_b
  #    + wp_pair_program_b
  #    + wp_td_tracking_b
  #    + wp_coding_stds_b
  #    + scenario_c2
  + (1 | session),
  family = negbinomial(),
  data = as.data.frame(d.only_submitted),
  prior = c(
    prior(normal(0, 1), class = "b"),
    prior(normal(0, 1), class = "Intercept"),
    prior(exponential(1), class = "sd"),
    prior(gamma(0.01,0.01), class = "shape") #default choice, dk if reasonable
  ),
  control = list(adapt_delta = 0.99),
  backend = "cmdstanr",
  chains = 4,
  cores = 4,
  iter = 5e3,
  #empty = TRUE
  file = "fits/sonarqube_issues0",
  file_refit = "on_change"
)

sonarqube_issues1 <- brm(
  sonarqube_issues ~ 1 
  + high_debt_version
      + mo(education_level)
      + education_field
      + work_domain
      + work_experience_programming
      + work_experience_java
      + workplace_peer_review
      + workplace_pair_programming
      + workplace_coding_standards
      + workplace_td_tracking
      + scenario
  + (1 | session),
  family = negbinomial(),
  data = as.data.frame(d.only_submitted),
  prior = c(
    prior(normal(0, 1), class = "b"),
    prior(normal(0, 1), class = "Intercept"),
    prior(exponential(1), class = "sd"),
    prior(gamma(0.01,0.01), class = "shape") #default choice, dk if reasonable
  ),
  control = list(adapt_delta = 0.99),
  backend = "cmdstanr",
  chains = 4,
  cores = 4,
  iter = 5e3,
  #empty = TRUE
  file = "fits/sonarqube_issues1",
  file_refit = "on_change"
)
